Session 2:
=========

git empty local repo

git init -->To initialize the local repo

Gitbash

git --version-->it will show git version--

Linux--> yum install -y git  , to install git in linux

cd~/Desktop--> Mac/Windows

cd ~-->Linux, we don't have desktop in linux

mkdir facebook

git init-->it is going to create git empty local repository

ls  -la 

.git file will create. It is a hidden directory

Once you created the local repo three logical arreas created.

working area
stagging area
local repo

git status -->it will show the status of the file
untracked--working area--red color

git add .
git add*

git add file name --> to move the file to stagging area, files will shown in green color
git add*.java

git status -->tracked files

git config --global user.name "venkat"
git config --global user.email "venky@gmail.com"

git config --global --list -->it will show details

it is authentication purpose, these details use who commited and what time

git commit -m "files moved"

How to map remote repo to local repo
git remote add aliasname url

git remote add facebook url

git remote -v

it will show the mapping from renote to local repo

git push aliasname master

git log --> how many commits to local repo

git log -2 latest 2 commits

git log filename


HEAD will points to latest commit id

git show commitid

git show --pretty="" --name-only commitid

How to get back to working area:
-----------------------
git reset-> to come from stagging area to working area
git reset file name-->this file will come from stagging to working area
git revert commitid-->it is going delete the newly added content from local repo, then push to remote repo.it will override the file..it will update the content







